@startuml c4-jotp-10c-dependency-graph
title JOTP - Dependency Graph (Which Primitives Depend on Others)

skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam linetype ortho

component Proc {
  note right
    Foundation
    All others depend
  end note
}

component ProcRef {
  note right
    Proc identity
  end note
}

component ProcLib {
  note right
    Startup protocol
    Initializes Proc
  end note
}

component Supervisor {
  note right
    Manages Proc instances
    Depends: Proc, ProcRef, ProcLib
  end note
}

component CrashRecovery {
  note right
    Recovery logic
    Depends: ProcLib, Supervisor
  end note
}

component ExitSignal {
  note right
    Signals from crashes
    Flows to Supervisor
  end note
}

component ProcessLink {
  note right
    Links Proc instances
    Bilateral dependencies
  end note
}

component ProcessMonitor {
  note right
    Monitors Proc
    Sends DOWN signals
  end note
}

component ProcessRegistry {
  note right
    Name registry
    Stores ProcRef instances
  end note
}

component StateMachine {
  note right
    State transitions
    Used by Proc handlers
  end note
}

component EventManager {
  note right
    Event dispatch
    Works with StateMachine
  end note
}

component ProcTimer {
  note right
    Timed messages
    Targets Proc mailboxes
  end note
}

component ProcSys {
  note right
    Introspection
    Queries Proc state
  end note
}

component Parallel {
  note right
    Fan-out execution
    Spawns multiple Proc
  end note
}

component Result {
  note right
    Error handling
    Used everywhere
  end note
}

ProcLib --> Proc: initializes
Supervisor --> ProcLib: uses
Supervisor --> Proc: manages
Supervisor --> CrashRecovery: uses

CrashRecovery --> ProcLib: restarts via
CrashRecovery --> ExitSignal: reads

ProcessLink -.-> Proc: links to/from
ProcessLink -.-> Proc: bilateral
ProcessMonitor --> Proc: monitors
ProcessMonitor --> ProcessRegistry: can integrate

ProcessRegistry --> ProcRef: stores
StateMachine --> StateMachine: pattern matches

EventManager --> StateMachine: routes to
EventManager --> Result: wraps in

ProcTimer --> Proc: sends_after to
ProcSys --> Proc: introspects

Parallel --> Proc: spawns multiple

Result -.-> Supervisor: wraps recovery
Result -.-> ProcLib: wraps startup
Result -.-> Proc: wraps operations
Result -.-> CrashRecovery: wraps restart

note bottom
  Core Dependencies:
  - Proc is the foundation
  - ProcRef identifies Proc
  - ProcLib initializes Proc
  - Supervisor manages groups of Proc
  - CrashRecovery restarts via ProcLib
  - ProcessRegistry stores ProcRef
  - StateMachine patterns in handlers
  - Result wraps all error-prone operations

  The 15 primitives form a coherent system
  where most operations ultimately work with
  Proc instances and their references
end note

@enduml
